author: COMSOL
description:
This model describes a tubular reactor where propylene oxide (A) reacts with water (B) to form propylene glycol (C): 

A + B -> C

Since water is the solvent and present in abundance, the reaction kinetics is described as first order with respect to propylene oxide

R = k*C_A

The reaction is exothermic and an isothermal cooling jacket is used to cool the reactor.

The reactor is modeled in 2D axisymmetry and the simulation results yield composition and temperature variations in both the radial and axial directions. The Chemistry interface is used to incorporate reaction kinetics and mass transport properties.
